The paper deals with generating synthetic versions of Twitter data using neural generative models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also addresses the issue of privacy and data protection, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on measures of risk and utility, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
